import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import re

request_headers = {
    'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64; rv:146.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/146.0'
}

clg_name = []
location = []
courses = []
ratings = []
fee = []
clg_type = []
entrance_exam = []

for page in range(1, 51):
    url = f'https://www.shiksha.com/engineering/colleges/b-tech-colleges-india-{page}'
    response = requests.get(url, headers=request_headers)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

    colleges = soup.find_all('div', class_='_8165')

    for college in colleges:

        # College name
        name = college.find('h3', class_='f7cc')
        clg_name.append(name.text.strip() if name else np.nan)

        # Location
        loc = college.find('span', class_='_5588')
        location.append(loc.text.strip() if loc else np.nan)

        # Course
        course = college.find('a', class_='_9865 ripple dark')
        courses.append(course.text.strip() if course else np.nan)

        # Rating
        rating = college.find('a', class_='_68c4 ripple dark')
        ratings.append(rating.text.strip() if rating else np.nan)

        # College type (Govt / Pvt)
        ctype = college.find('div', class_='edfa')
        if ctype:
            match = re.findall(r'Govt|Pvt', ctype.text)
            clg_type.append(match[0] if match else np.nan)
        else:
            clg_type.append(np.nan)

        # Entrance exam
        exam = college.find('ul', class_='_0954')
        entrance_exam.append(exam.text.strip() if exam else np.nan)

        # Fee
        fee_tag = college.find('div', class_='dcfd')
        if fee_tag:
            fee_match = re.findall(r'\d+\.\d+\sL|\d+\sL', fee_tag.text)
            fee.append(fee_match[0] if fee_match else np.nan)
        else:
            fee.append(np.nan)

# Create DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame({
    'clg_name': clg_name,
    'location': location,
    'fee': fee,
    'ratings': ratings,
    'courses': courses,
    'clg_type': clg_type,
    'entrance_exam': entrance_exam
})

df = pd.read_csv('engineering_colleges.csv')

import pandas as pd

df = pd.read_csv("engineering_colleges.csv")

# Convert fee "3.28 L" -> numeric
df["fee_num"] = df["fee"].str.replace(" L", "").astype(float)

pivot1 = pd.pivot_table(df, values="fee_num", index="location", aggfunc="mean")
